{"type":"message","id":"bf9b1821","parentId":"be2f5ef6","timestamp":"2026-03-03T06:03:00.336Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ncudg7yxj29_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\nconst API_BASE = 'https://qveris.ai/api/v1';\nconst API_KEY = process.env.QVERIS_API_KEY;\n\nasync function search(query, limit = 10) {\n  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/search`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': `Bearer ${API_KEY}`\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ query, limit })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  return data;\n}\n\nasync function execute(toolId, params, searchId = null) {\n  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/tools/execute`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': `Bearer ${API_KEY}`\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ tool_id: toolId, params, search_id: searchId })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  return data;\n}\n\nasync function getByIds(...ids) {\n  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/tools/get-by-ids`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': `Bearer ${API_KEY}`\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ ids })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  return data;\n}\n\nconst cmd = process.argv[2];\nconst args = process.argv.slice(3);\n\nasync function main() {\n  try {\n    if (cmd === 'search') {\n      const query = args[0];\n      const limit = args.includes('--limit') ? parseInt(args[args.indexOf('--limit') + 1]) : 10;\n      const result = await search(query, limit);\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n    } else if (cmd === 'execute') {\n      const toolId = args[0];\n      const searchIdIdx = args.indexOf('--search-id');\n      const searchId = searchIdIdx > -1 ? args[searchIdIdx + 1] : null;\n      const paramsIdx = args.indexOf('--params');\n      const params = paramsIdx > -1 ? JSON.parse(args[paramsIdx + 1]) : {};\n      const result = await execute(toolId, params, searchId);\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n    } else if (cmd === 'get-by-ids') {\n      const result = await getByIds(...args.filter(a => !a.startsWith('--')));\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n    } else {\n      console.error('Unknown command:', cmd);\n      process.exit(1);\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('Error:', err.message);\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n}\n\nmain();\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772517780334}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad007e5f","parentId":"bf9b1821","timestamp":"2026-03-03T06:03:09.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the script uses JSON.parse on the params. The issue might be related to how the shell is handling the quotes. Let me try a different approach - maybe I need to use single quotes around the JSON object differently, or escape things.\n\nActually, let me try using a simpler approach - maybe the API itself is expecting something different. Let me look at the error message more carefully: \"缺少必需的查询参数: 'codes'\" - this is coming from the API side, not from my parameter parsing.\n\nWait - let me think about this differently. Maybe the QVeris API itself is returning this error because it's having issues connecting to the iFinD backend. Let me try a simpler test with a single stock code.","thinkingSignature":"011cfa5f247ad64dfac2811b9b700cc0771c8bdf14ba67edb597121107719903"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7nw5jmjiaw5u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace && node -e \"\nconst API_KEY = process.env.QVERIS_API_KEY;\nconst API_BASE = 'https://qveris.ai/api/v1';\n\nasync function execute() {\n  const res = await fetch(API_BASE + '/tools/execute', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + API_KEY\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      tool_id: 'ths_ifind.real_time_quotation.v1',\n      params: { codes: '002149.SZ' }\n    })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n}\n\nexecute();\n\"","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":14087,"output":340,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772517780336}}
