{"type":"message","id":"d4496918","parentId":"ba27a378","timestamp":"2026-03-03T06:03:19.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The same error persists even with a direct Node.js call. This seems to be an API-side issue with the iFinD tool. The error message \"缺少必需的查询参数: 'codes'\" is coming from the QVeris API itself, which might mean there's a problem with how the iFinD service is configured on their end.\n\nLet me try a different tool - maybe the historical+realtime one (ths_ifind.quotation.v1) which has more parameters but might work better.","thinkingSignature":"e8e908368b52d50d8e1fb3c8a48f14942e0b1bde0634050f66583b5c98e01e20"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t2h88mkigug0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace && node -e \"\nconst API_KEY = process.env.QVERIS_API_KEY;\nconst API_BASE = 'https://qveris.ai/api/v1';\n\nasync function execute() {\n  const res = await fetch(API_BASE + '/tools/execute', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + API_KEY\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      tool_id: 'ths_ifind.quotation.v1',\n      params: { \n        codes: '002149.SZ',\n        startdate: '2026-03-03',\n        enddate: '2026-03-03'\n      }\n    })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n}\n\nexecute();\n\"","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":14558,"output":319,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772517790099}}
